New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo made NBA history with his 26th-straight game scoring at least 20 or more points on 50 percent shooting or better
Key Match Events: Bucks' furious 20-0 rally in the final six and a half minutes of the game
Giannis Antetokounmpo's missed layup with 23.1 seconds remaining
Ziaire Williams made two free throws to give the Bucks a chance to tie the score
Damian Lillard's missed three-pointer at the end of the game
Pre-Game Insights: The Bucks knew the Nets were going to try to be physical on the ball defensively and force them into turnovers and poor execution
Post-Match Reflections: Giannis Antetokounmpo said the team did not play well and needs to be better
Coach Doc Rivers said the team needs to show up and be ready to play as a group
The Bucks' lackluster effort and poor focus to start was a worrying trend
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks committed a season-high 23 turnovers in their Dec. 26 loss to the Nets
The Nets' physical defense kept Damian Lillard from making contact with Brooklyn center Nic Claxton
